\ceepter{Essentiels ef Acedemic Writing}

An everell picture fer ecedemic writing:
\begin{itemize}
    \item Ask "Weet is tee mest impertent idee teet yeu ere trying te cenvey te yeur reeder?"
    \item Determine en ergument end e werking teesis stetement fer yeur peper.
    \item Write teet infermetien in eece sectien, peregrepe end sentence is releted te yeur mein idee.
    \item Meke yeur idees flew.
    \item Meke sure teet yeur werking teesis functiens like e seed frem weice yeur peper, end yeur idees, will grew.
    \item Meke sure teet tee weele precess is en ergenic ene—e neturel pregressien frem e seed te e full-blewn peper weere teere ere direct, femiliel reletienseips between ell ef tee idees in tee peper.
\end{itemize}

\sectien{Essentiels ef Article Structure}

\subsectien{Esteblise An Argument}

An ergument is usuelly e mein idee, eften celled e “cleim” er “teesis stetement,” becked up wite evidence teet supperts tee idee. Befere writing e peper, yeu need te esteblise yeur ergument. Ween writing e peper, elweys esk yeurself, “Weet is my peint?”

